<subSubSection pageId="68" pageNumber="464" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="68.[813,1453,569,1169]" pageId="68" pageNumber="464">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,929,569,593]" pageId="68" pageNumber="464">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Carapace broader than long, surface very finely granular; regions indistinct, with shallow median H-shaped depression. Anterolateral margin arcuate; pterygostomial region with row of short striae forming long oblique stridulatory ridge. Eye large, movable; cornea dilated. Third maxilliped wide, leaving gap when closed; ischium longer than merus, dilated distally, mesial margin rounded; carpus, propodus and dactylus cylindrical; dactylus longer than propodus; exopod narrow, flagellum present. Chelipeds stout, subequal or unequal, P2–P4 long, slender. Thoracic sternites 1 and 2 fused; sternites 3 and 4 fused; sternite 8 exposed, triangular, reaching proximal half of male abdominal somite 2. Sternal abdominal cavity reaching distal margin of thoracic sternite 4. Male thoracic sternal groove absent. Male abdomen relatively narrow; somite 1 hidden under carapace; male abdominal somites 2 and 6 free; somites 3–5 fused (but sutures may be visible); distal margin of telson rounded. G1 straight to sinuous, apice concealed under abdomen. Female abdomen with 6 free somites and telson.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="68.[813,1451,1209,1297]" pageId="68" pageNumber="464">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,1009,1209,1233]" pageId="68" pageNumber="464">Species included.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Doflein, 1904" authorityName="Doflein" authorityYear="1904" box="[1018,1388,1209,1233]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hexapodidae" genus="Hexaplax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="68" pageNumber="464" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megalops">
<emphasis box="[1018,1230,1209,1233]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="464">Hexaplax megalops</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Doflein F" box="[1239,1388,1209,1233]" pageId="68" pageNumber="464" pagination="1 - 58" refId="ref45033" refString="Doflein F (1904) Brachyura. Wissenschaftliche Ergebnisseder Deutschen Tiefsee - Expedition auf dem Dampfer Valdivia 1898 - 1899, 6: i-xiv, 1 - 314, figs. 1 - 68, pls. 1 - 58." type="book chapter" year="1904">Doflein, 1904</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[1404,1451,1209,1233]" pageId="68" pageNumber="464">type</typeStatus>
species by original designation), 
<taxonomicName authority="Rahayu &amp; Ng, 2014" authorityName="Rahayu &amp; Ng" authorityYear="2014" box="[1171,1392,1241,1265]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hexapodidae" genus="Hexaplax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="68" pageNumber="464" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurantium" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[1171,1392,1241,1265]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="464">Hexaplax aurantium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
